question: How many agreement have signed between India and Palestine?
explanation: India and Palestine have signed six agreements on the infrastructural development in the Palestine. A MOU was signed by the two countries for the construction of an India Palestine Centre for empowering women, "Turathi" at a cost of USD 5 million. A MOU for setting up of a new National Printing Press at Ramallah at a cost of USD 5 million was also signed between the two nations.
